	adding getTags() methods to Area and Module that return dictionaries of all used tags they contain, organized by object type
	changing Module to retrieve the list of areas from the IFO file, not by looking through all the resources of the module

2005-03-12 12:55  sumpfork

	* AUTHORS:

	add alan to authors

2005-03-12 12:46  sumpfork

	* run/: nevercommand, neveredit, neverscript, runmodule:

	attempt to replace mac os specific 'pythonw' call with cross-platform version
	this version checks whether it's on Mac OS, and re-executes itself using 'pythonw' if appropriate
	this behaviour can be turned off with --disable_pythonw
	also some untested preference setting code for nevercommand

2005-03-12 11:12  brab

	* game/: Conversation.py, Creature.py:

	I was wrong: a speaker tag is a tag, hence a CExoString (unless there is a way
	to grab all creature tags from a module). However a creature TemplateResRef is
	a ResRef,UTC, not a ResRef,NSS.

